CatDescriptText: Cutline of related images published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 28, 1951, pg. 11, reads: "Jabberwocky Jabberwock...was truly gay this year with A. Leo Weil School housing the amusing annual event presented by Delta Sigma Theta sorors... - Harris Photos." Article reads: "AKAs Capture First Prize in Jabberwock - Curiousity [Curiosity]? Yes, that was the theme of the Delta Sigma Theta's first Jabberwock in five years and it was a tremendous comeback.  The affair was held Friday, April 20 and was a night of fun and laughter for Pittsburghers...."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of man wearing tuxedo on left, and women wearing gowns standing on risers, on stage, at A. Leo Weil School, for Delta Sigma Theta's Jabberwock
